Description.note: A Bramin who has made a vow to wear an iron collar of 2 4 pound weight and 4 foot square, till such time as he shall have a massâ€™d by alms money sufficient to build an hospital.  A Bramin who swings himself out of devotion for half an hour in honour of the God Eswara over a fire which he feeds with wood he had placed on both sides of him.  A Bramin who has had himself shackled to the foot of a tree with an iron chain with a resolution to end his days in that posture.  Two Bramins of the family of the Soudraes, called Joguis dragging after them long heavy chains, which go from the leg where they are fastned over the shoulder.

Title: Another She-Penitent sitting in a very uneasy posture, which she is not allowed to change.
Description.note: Another She-Penitent sitting in a very uneasy posture, which she is not allowed to change. A penitent She-Bramin, who stands forever in the same posture, a devotee, attended by her maid, comes to recommend herself to her prayers.  A pilgrim among the Bramins.  A penitent who stands with his hands over his head till he dies.  Posture in which the penitent sleep without ever stooping their arms.
